<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideefc1f61-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s1765"><num value="1765">§ 1765.</num><heading> Foreign service appropriations; applicability</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Provisions in annual appropriation Acts of the Department of State facilitating the work of the Foreign Service of the United States shall be applicable under rules and regulations prescribed by the President or his designee to activities pursuant to this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ideefc1f62-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-28/ch1041">Aug. 28, 1954, ch. 1041</ref>, title VI, § 605, <ref href="/us/stat/68/909">68 Stat. 909</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/501/tIII/s301/4">Pub. L. 95–501, title III, § 301(4)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-21">Oct. 21, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1688">92 Stat. 1688</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
